post_text: Thank you to the Minnesota Grocers Association and Chris' Food Center for their donations and continued support to the East Central Backpack Program. #isd2580
shared_text:
East Central Secondary Counseling Department
September 10 at 2:40 PM ·

Thank you to the Minnesota Grocers Association and Chris' Food Center for their donation to the East Central Backpack Program. Chris' Food Center is one of 18 companies in MN to be recognized for their exceptional efforts to end Hunger in their communities. They received the Silver Plate Award for Best Overall Program Support in which the program of their choice will receive a donation!

We are so grateful for all the work and support Chris' Food Center has and continues to provide for our community, especially the backpack food program!

Accepting the donation from Craig and Kristee Thorvig are this year's NHS officers- President Emma Jansen, Vice President Lori Grundmeier, Secretary/PR Dez LeTexier, and Treasurer Cassidee Thorvig!

post_text:
East Central School District is seeking applications to fill a vacancy on the School Board.

Requirements to Apply
Interested parties should fill out an Affidavit of Candidacy (available on website or District Office) and answer the following question in written form:

“Why do you want to be a member of the East Central School Board?”

Submit written response via email to kzemke@eastcentral.k12.mn.us or drop off at the District Office.

Term/Timeline
The new board member will be appointed and take oath of office on November 16th until the board holds a special election in November of 2021. That election will be to finish out the remainder of the term, which is December 31st, 2023

Application deadline: September 9, 2020

post_text:
Governor Walz has issued an executive order requiring face masks in all public indoor spaces. This applies to schools as well. Beginning on Friday, July 24th at 11:59pm, if you are on the school campus a face mask is required. There are exceptions to the mask rule for those with medical conditions when masks would create a health risk. Attached is the Governor's Executive Order outlining the details of our masking requirements. I know decisions like this can elicit strong feelings on both sides of the issue. Some will strongly agree and some will strongly disagree. As a school system we will comply with this order and trust the direction of our state level leaders. Our community and our kids will respond how we respond.

Minnesota Superintendents were told today Governor Walz will announce the fall reopening scenario (In Person, Hybrid, or Distance Learning) next Thursday, July 30th. Please look for an update from Superintendent Almos following that decision. #isd2580 #YourFutureOurFocus #eaglesstrong

https://www.leg.state.mn.us/archive/execorders/20-81.pdf

Wednesday, June 24th from 2:00 p.m. - 3:30 p.m. and Friday, June 26th from 8:00 a.m. - 9:30 a.m. Click the link to learn more and register: https://bit.ly/30zs3gQ

post_text: Do you have a mini muffin or cupcake pan at home? Try this delicious recipe from Mrs. Finley. Don't forget to like her page to follow along on weekly FACS tips and tricks.
shared_text:
FACS Finley
May 7 at 10:43 AM ·

This week culinary students were sent home a donut baking kit!

I took a guess that most families don't have a donut pan, thus students have been challenged to see what kind of pans work! I personally made them using both a mini muffin pan and a cupcake pan.

If you want to be like my culinary students, here is the recipe they are using! https://www.foodnetwork.com/recipes/ina-garten/cinnamon-baked-doughnuts-recipe-2135621

post_text:
Hello to all of my East Central friends! I miss you all so much! And I miss school, too. I am staying at home, just like all of you, in hopes that everyone stays well and stays safe. I can't wait to see you all again (and of course I can't wait for you to smile at me and pet me!) but until we can be together again, I just want you to know that I am thinking about each and every one of you. I could not have asked for better friends. Every one of you is so very special to me. This is hard for all of us, but I know we can do this together! Eagles Strong!

Love, Norm

post_text:
Dear East Central Parents,

Below is a link to a brief survey that we are asking each family to complete now that our distance learning plan has been in full effect for some time. The purpose of the survey is to help us understand the effectiveness of and discover the barriers that still may exist to our distance learning program relative to Internet access and devices your students are using. Participation is optional, but your response will help us provide better instructional opportunities for your students. We expect this survey to take approximately 5 minutes to complete. Thank you for your participation and for all you are doing to help your children continue their learning.

This survey is being conducted by ECMECC, which East Central is a member of. The survey is being done in Pine, Chisago, Kanabec, Isanti and Mille Lacs counties.

http://bit.ly/20distancelearning

If you have any questions regarding this survey, please contact Bill Groskreutz, Director of Technology via email at bill@eastcentral.k12.mn.us or by phone at 320.245.6038.

This spring has brought forth many challenges for all of us at East Central. At this time we have canceled our yearly preschool round up. This event is a great opportunity for parents and children to tour the school and classrooms and meet the teachers. We still encourage parents to complete registration forms for their child who will be starting either 3-year-old or 4-year-old preschool next fall. Children must be 3 or 4 years of age by September 1, 2020. Opportunities for tours may become available as the quarantine uplifts. Registration forms can be found on the school’s website at www.eastcentral.k12.mn.us. Please feel free to contact me with any questions or concerns.

Jennie Carlin
Early Childhood Teacher/Coordinator
320-245-2289 ext.6104
jcarlin@eastcentral.k12.mn.us

post_text:
Dear East Central Families,
I sure hope you are all doing well, my thoughts are with all of you and wishing the students could be here at school. I shared a few pictures with you. I talk about my cats, Vinny and Chewy a lot so I wanted to include them. I have been doing a lot of puzzles at home - here is Vinny helping me. I, of course, wanted to share a picture of Ms. Amber and me from this past Halloween. We are here working and trying to organize the distant learning.
The buses are delivering food (lunch & breakfast) and the homework packets went out today (Monday 3/30)! We are all trying to navigate this new type of school, so please email or call if you have questions. Teachers will be contacting families at least 2 times per week - if you need more support just let us know. Send the completed work back, put in the envelopes we sent home and we will be sending out new packets next week. Stay safe and healthy and send me pictures of kids working at home - I will post on the Facebook page. Thanks - Mrs. Chryst

post_text:
The East Central Dollars for Scholars committee is proud to announce that the 2020 scholarship application is now available.

These scholarships are made possible by the generous financial contributions of community members, business owners, educators, students, alumni, and the work of dedicated East Central Dollars for Scholars volunteers.

Scholarships are available to EC Seniors who have taken the ACT test and have earned a minimum of 6 high school credits and EC graduates currently in college carrying a minimum of 12 semester credits. College graduate students are not eligible for the scholarship program. The application is available and must be submitted online at eastcentral.dollarsforscholars.org.

Deadline is March 20, 2020.

In December EC students volunteered for the annual Dollars for Scholars Phone-a-thon. This event raises funds for scholarships awarded to students annually. Students who volunteer are eligible for a door prize. This year’s door prize winners of $25 were: (left to right) Elaine Wittenberg, Gabe Koland, and Cassidee Thorvig. #isd2580

Reminder: Elementary students will be going sledding on Friday, January 24th as their PBIS reward for Quarter 2.

Please make sure your child has appropriate clothing to be outside and in the snow.

If parents would like to join and go sledding or just watch you are welcome to meet us at Lion’s Hill.

Students can bring their own sleds, but they need to be dropped off at Lion’s Hill. We do have some sleds students can use. No sleds can be brought on the bus.

Approximate sledding times are as follows:
Grades K & 1: 9:15 – 10:15 am
Grades 4 & 5: 10:30 – 11:30 am
Grades 2 & 3: 12:25 – 1:25 pm
Grades 6: 1:45 – 2:45 pm

post_text:
This Saturday, December 7th, East Central Dollars for Scholars will be holding their 26th Annual Phone-a-thon.

East Central Dollars for Scholars is a locally operated and supported non-profit scholarship organization committed to expanding educational opportunities for East Central High School graduates. Each year we grant scholarships to dozens of graduates and post-graduates who are pursuing higher educational opportunities at universities, vocational and community colleges, and trade schools. Recipients are selected on the basis of academic achievement and participation in school, work, and community activities.

Last year, 47 students were awarded $110,724 in scholarships, thanks to the generous donations of local organizations, businesses, and community members like you.

Your gift, whether it is $10, $25, $50, or more, reflects your pride in our students and your commitment to the ongoing education of our future leaders.

Donations can be made at:
eastcentral.dollarsforscholars.org

or mailed to:
East Central Dollars for Scholars
PO Box 4
Askov, MN 55704

Amanda Thompson is with Sami Koland and Cassie Gaede.
November 21, 2019 at 1:56 PM ·

NJHS and NHS members (East Central’s National Honor Societies) spent the morning volunteering at Feed My Starving Children. They prepared, packaged, and boxed Manna Packs of rice meals. These amazing students packed 46 boxes! That will feed about 27 children in Nicaragua for a year.

post_text: Did you know today is the global literacy event Read for the Record? This event brings together millions of adults and children around the world each year to read the same book on the same day in order to raise awareness about the critical importance of early literacy. This year Jumpstart is celebrating their 14th anniversary with the book Thank You, Omu!, a heart-warming story of generosity and community. Mrs. Schmidt is sharing the book during her classes.#isd2580
